The paper focuses on the effectiveness of different tutorial types for software developers, which is a topic that falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HCI) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the study involves the use of questionnaires and statistical analysis, which could also place it in the categories of education (cs.ED) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the study involves the use of a software tool, which could potentially place it in the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
